==English==
===Etymology===
Originally a person that is sent in advance to provide lodgings, from ''herberge'' "army encampment". See also German ''[[Herberge]]''.
=== Noun ===
'''harbinger''', (''plural'': harbingers)
#a person or thing that [[foreshadow]]s or [[foretell]]s the coming of someone or something
